recipieName: Fried egg on toast with apple, yogurt & latte
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Eggs, 1 large (1.8oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
  • Sriracha, 1 tsp(s), optional (0.2oz)
  • Apple, 1 small (5.3oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, ⅓ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Latte, plain, nonfat milk, 1 small takeaway cup(s) (11.5oz)
recipeInstructions:

Remove the egg from the pan and place on top of warm toasted bread. Drizzle over sriracha, if using.

Follow with a skim latte.

recipeIngredients:
• Old fashioned (rolled) oats, ½ cup(s) (1.4oz)
  • Chia seeds, 1 tbsp(s) (0.4oz)

recipieName: Chicken stir-fry with greens
recipeIngredients:

recipieName: Pear & berry overnight oats with walnuts
recipeIngredients:
• Old fashioned (rolled) oats, 1 cup(s) (2.8oz)
  • 1% milk, 1 cup(s) (8.3fl oz)
  • Pear, 2 small, shredded (10.4oz)
  • Ground nutmeg, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, 3 cup(s) (1.5lb)
  • Walnuts, 10 walnut(s), chopped (0.7oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 1 tbsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Frozen berries, any type, 1 cup(s), frozen or fresh (6.9oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Pear & berry overnight oats with walnuts according to recipe instructions below. 

Portion into 4 separate containers or jars and refrigerate overnight so that you can grab and go in the morning.

When ready to eat, grab one container or jar. Spoon into bowl, or if jar is large enough top with ½ cup of yogurt, ¼ cup berries and 1 teaspoon of nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

Follow with a takeaway coffee, or a latte made at home with 1 cup of milk.

TIP: For cooler days, warm overnight oats in the microwave.

Pear & berry overnight oats with walnuts instructions

Place oats into a bowl or container. Add the milk, pear, nutmeg and 1 cup of the yogurt. Stir to combine. Cover and place in the fridge overnight to soak.

To toast walnuts and sesame seeds, heat a small skillet over medium heat. Toast, stirring 2 to 3 minutes until golden, being careful not to burn. Remove skillet from heat and allow to cool. Chop walnuts into small pieces. Store nut and seed mix in the fridge in a small airtight container.

When ready to eat, divide oat mixture between 4 bowls. Top each bowl with ½ cup of yogurt, ¼ cup of berries, and toasted nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

TIP: Prepared overnight oats will keep for 5 days. Place oat mixture and the nut and seed mix into separate airtight containers and store in the fridge. When you're ready to eat, assemble and add the remaining ingredients.

recipieName: Mezze plate with falafels, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus
recipeIngredients:
• Red bell pepper, raw, 2 medium, sliced (8.4oz)
  • Asparagus, 1 bunch(es), trimmed (4oz)
  • Zucchini, 2 medium, cut into sticks (13.8oz)
  • Canned chickpeas, 1½ cup(s), drained and rinsed (8.7oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Lemon, ½ medium, juiced and zested for hummus (1.5oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, ¼ cup(s) (0.2oz)
  • Psyllium husk, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Cumin, ground, ½ tsp(s)
  • Allspice, ¼ tsp(s)
  • Dried cilantro, ½ tsp(s)
  • Cayenne pepper, ¼ tsp(s)
  • Black pepper, 2 dash(es)
  • Paprika, ¼ tsp(s)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Mezze plate with falafels, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Transfer remaining two servings to an airtight container and keep in the fridge for later in the week.

Mezze plate with falafel, grilled vegetables & homemade hummus instructions

Preheat the broiler to medium-high, then place the bell pepper, asparagus and zucchini on a baking tray and cook for 5 to 6 minutes, turning halfway through, then place to one side and leave to cool. Turn the oven to 350°F.

To make the falafel, in a food processor, blitz 1 cup of the chickpeas, 1 tablespoons of olive oil, ¼ of the lemon juiced, fresh cilantro, psyllium and garlic, as well as the cumin, allspice, dried cilantro and cayenne. Taste, and season with black pepper if desired. Form the mix into 6 small falafels, roughly the same size, and bake for 30 minutes, or until cooked through.

To make the homemade chunky hummus, mash ½ cup of the chickpeas in a small bowl. Add ¼ of the lemon juiced and zested, paprika and 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Alternatively blitz everything in a food processor until it has a chunky 'dip' consistency.

Enjoy 2 falafels and a third of the hummus and vegetable for dinner. Refrigerate the remaining two servings.

recipieName: Cheese & spinach omelet
recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 2 large (3.5oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Baby spinach, 1 cup(s) (0.7oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, 1 tbsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
recipeInstructions:
Crack the eggs into a bowl, season with pepper and whisk. Stir in the baby spinach and cheddar cheese.

Heat the olive oil in a small non-stick skillet over medium heat and swirl to coat.

Pour in the egg mixture. Swirl the pan to evenly coat the base with the eggs. Using a spatula, lift the cooked egg and allow uncooked egg to flow underneath. Cook the egg mixture for about 3 minutes, until partially set. Flip with a spatula and cook for a further 2 to 3 minutes. Reduce heat to low, and continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes, or until done to your liking. 

Once cooked, fold omelet in half and serve with warm toast.

recipieName: Turkey & bean taco casserole
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 2 tbsp(s) (1oz)
  • Extra lean ground turkey, raw, 6 oz(s) (6oz)
  • Red onion, 1 small, chopped (2.1oz)
  • Green bell pepper, ½ pepper(s), chopped (2oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, ½ medium, chopped (2.1oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 small, chopped (4.2oz)
  • Taco seasoning, 2 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Red kidney beans, ⅓ cup(s), rinsed and drained (2.1oz)
  • Low sodium chicken stock, 2 cup(s) (1.1lb)
  • Cauliflower rice, 2 cup(s) (6.9oz)
  • Cilantro, fresh, 1 cup(s) (0.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Turkey & bean taco casserole according to recipe instructions below.

Store the cooked turkey and vegetables in a container in the fridge. Store the remaining cauliflower rice and cilantro in separate airtight containers in the fridge for later in the week.

Turkey & bean taco casserole instructions

Heat the oil in a deep non-stick skillet over medium-high heat and add the turkey and onion. Cook, stirring and breaking up any ground turkey lumps with the back of a spoon, for 3 minutes or until the onion is softened but not browned.

Stir in the bell peppers, zucchini, seasoning, beans and stock and bring to a simmer. Simmer, partially covered and stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Remove the lid, continue to simmer, uncovered and stirring occasionally, for another 10 minutes or until the vegetables are tender and the stock has reduced by two-thirds.

Heat the cauliflower rice according to packet instructions. Divide the cauliflower rice and casserole between bowls. Top with the cilantro and serve.
